    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Who's the Disciple?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Deepak Chopra letter disputes James Atlas's August 7 Op-Ed article on Vice Pres Al Gore's reading habits</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>James Atlas, in his Aug. 7 Op-Ed article about Al Gore's reading habits, says one of Mr. Gore's ''new favorites is 'The Marriage of Sense and Soul,' by Ken Wilber, a disciple of Deepak Chopra.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>James Atlas, in his Aug. 7 Op-Ed article about Al Gore's reading habits, says one of Mr. Gore's ''new favorites is 'The Marriage of Sense and Soul,' by Ken Wilber, a disciple of Deepak Chopra.''</p>
        <p>I am Ken Wilber's disciple, not the other way around.</p>
        <p>DEEPAK CHOPRA  La Jolla, Calif., Aug. 14, 2000</p>
      </block>
